-- Emlak Konut Property Hires TSKB, UniCredit for Turkish Public Offering
-- Ercan Ersoy
-- 2010-06-28T11:35:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/emlak-konut-property-hires-tskb-unicredit-for-turkish-public-offering.html

          
          
             Emlak Konut Gayrimenkul Yatirim
Ortakligi, a Turkish property developer, hired UniCredit SpA and
 Turkiye Sinai Kalkinma Bankasi AS  to sell shares to the public.  
 Emlak Konut, owned by the state-run housing authority, will
hold a news conference to announce the sale plan with the two
banks in Istanbul on July 2, according to an e-mailed statement
by the company today.  
 Emlak Konut will sell a minimum 25 percent stake and
expects to raise at least 2 billion liras ($1.3 billion) from
the sale,  Dunya  newspaper reported on May 6 citing general
manager Murat Kurum.  
